The paper is about generative modeling, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of autoencoders and optimal transport suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The focus on image generation and comparison to GANs suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of "cs.CV" (Computer Vision). The use of non-adversarial methods and comparison to other generative models suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the use of optimal transport suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of "cs.IT" (Information Theory).
